Governor Ibrahim Gaidam of Yobe state has ordered a 12-hour restriction of vehicular movement in preparation for peaceful and hitch-free Eid-el-Kabir prayers across the state. In a statement by the Director General of Press Affairs to the Governor, Malam Abdullahi Bego, he said the restriction begins from 10.00pm tonight till 10.00am on Tuesday (tomorrow). He said vehicular restriction followed a security meeting that the governor had with heads of security, intelligence and law enforcement agencies in the state. "The public is kindly advised that no vehicle will be allowed within or near Eid prayer grounds except those on special duties. "His Excellency, Governor Ibrahim Gaidam wishes the Muslim Ummah a peaceful and memorable Eid-el-Kabir festival," he added.